A few days ago I asked people to suggest me some songs to make a cover of, here on Instagram. I realized thereupon that i have been forgetting this beautiful song. So now i had to go all the way down my songs library to find this song (which was ironically already there). Then i couldn't resist learning this song and making a cover after. This video is just me when i sing. Although i sang the song and made a video (obviously singing) at different instants of time. Y'all must be wondering why am i looking away at times, yo imma looking at the lyrics. Welcoming every kind of feedback. Enjoy🤍 and share.

latestPosts.caption:
Past two months have been so meaningful and fulfilling for me.

Here’s why-

I joined @ankurwarikoo ‘s team and it was immensely insightful, lovely and a lot of working my ass off!

But this is just what you see. So, you can’t even guess how great of a deal this is to me.

Here’s the whole thing-

Two years ago, I discovered Ankur on YouTube. Consumed a lot of his content till this time, graduated from his content (people who work with him will know this).

A year ago, I discovered the team behind him, Waricrew. Researched about this team and instantly wanted to be a part of the same!

Constantly followed both of these brands on all platforms to know more about them.

Also, until this, I considered Ankur a solid role model :) Something which never felt real before. Truly because he is inspiring, insanely humble and that both of us share a common interest— physics (which we both decided to discontinue later in life).

6 months ago, I connected to the team (vora.cious helped me big time!). Wrote Ankur a mail, people following him know the significance of cold emailing him ;)

Nothing happened.

2 months ago, I asked around and got to know there’s an opening in his team. Instantly applied for it (their hiring process is very elaborative and just makes too much sense!)

Got selected and worked my ass off till now. Extremely excited knowing that I’ll get to meet him and the brilliant team in September!

But last two months didn’t go as I had expected. I moved out of home for a new opportunity, simultaneously worked with Waricrew and not to forget my own content creation on IG and YT🤍

Three days ago, we had a team offsite and also met the founding batch of the course “How To LinkedIn” with which we were busy.

The social animal in me was so happy to interact with all these brilliant people!

Got so many things to take back home, “bittersweet” memories, all these pictures and videos with my storage full, a terrarium plant (thanks to @surabhisolankii 🤍), a gift from Kasol by @zaksagar and many more.

What a journey man.

Loved it thoroughly, can’t wait for more :)

#ankurwarikoo #waricrew #warikoo
